The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Saturday, July 17, 2004  Fiasco resolved, races today 
 FROM WILLIAM TELL				 										Bangalore: The Bangalore Turf Club (BTC) and the Bangalore Trainers Association fiasco was temporarily resolved on Friday morning, thanks to Thursdays unofficial late night parleys between the BTC chief steward Harindra Shetty and the aggrieved trainers. Shetty, it is learnt, had given verbal assurance to trainers that their demands, pertaining to modification of medication rules, would be addressed to. In the past such verbal commitments were hardly respected. It is a temporary truce, said a BTC trainer who did not want to be named.				 										Racing, therefore, will be held here as scheduled during the weekend and nine events have been framed in Saturdays card which features the 1,200m S.M. Ramakrishna Rao Memorial Cup. However, it is Michael Eshwers Star Alone who is fancied to win the trophy in the hands of K.P. Appu.				 										SELECTIONS				 										2 pm: Keep Guessing 1. Inkwazi 2. Sensitive Prince 3.				 										2.30 pm: Galaxy Star 1. Accordance 2.				 										3 pm: Candramala 1. Zenda 2. Serious Attraction 3.				 										3.30 pm: Minstrel Girl 1. Warsaw Pact 2. Eden 3.				 										4 pm: Star Alone 1. Aerospace 2. Star Wind 3.				 										4.30 pm: Jism 1. Star Ballad 2. So Ravishing 3.				 										5 pm: Beautiful Crown 1. Friendly Fire 2. Beyond Limits 3.				 										5.30 pm: Star Of Treasure 1. Waves Of Glory 2. Copper Bracelet 3.				 										6 pm: Clarentia 1. Candragupta 2. Diamond Tops 3.				 										Days Best: Clarentia Double: Galaxy Star amp; Minstrel Girl
